# California State University, Long Beach

A [public](/Public_university) [research university](/Research_university) nestled in the rather specific locale of [Long Beach, California](/Long_Beach,_California), United States, [California State University, Long Beach](/California_State_University,_Long_Beach) (CSULB) is perhaps better known in the ephemeral realm of [athletics as](/Long_Beach_State_athletics) Long Beach State University (LBSU). This institution, a sprawling testament to academic ambition, sits on a 322-acre campus – a considerable chunk of real estate, making it the second largest in the venerable [California State University](/California_State_University) (CSU) system.

**Former Designations and Enduring Identity**

Before settling into its current nomenclature, this institution cycled through several identities, much like a person trying on personalities before realizing they’re all equally disappointing. Initially conceived in 1949 as the Los Angeles-Orange County State College, a name that perfectly captured its geographic ambiguity, it quickly streamlined to Long Beach State College by 1950. The mid-1960s saw another shift, becoming California State College, [at] Long Beach in 1964, a subtle distinction that likely kept many an administrator occupied. By 1972, it had matured into its present form, [California State University, Long Beach](/California_State_University,_Long_Beach).

